External knowledge: 
- "most cited published works from the past year" refers to publications that have been cited at least once in the past year and have a status of 'published';
- "other relevant details" include journal name, volume, issue, pages, and average accesses per citation;
- "metrics" are the key statistics used for evaluating the publications, including citation counts, unique authors, unique accesses, and the average accesses per citation.
